title: Google\Cloud\AppEngine\V1\UrlMap
name: UrlMap
description:
URL pattern and description of how the URL should be handled. App Engine can handle URLs by executing application code or by serving static files uploaded with the version, such as images, CSS, or JavaScript.

Generated from protobuf message google.appengine.v1.UrlMap

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.url_regex
params.description: URL prefix. Uses regular expression syntax, which means regexp special characters must be escaped, but should not contain groupings. All URLs that begin with this prefix are handled by this handler, using the portion of the URL after the prefix as part of the file path.

params.name: data.static_files
params.description: Returns the contents of a file, such as an image, as the response.

params.name: data.script
params.description: Executes a script to handle the requests that match this URL pattern. Only the auto value is supported for Node.js in the App Engine standard environment, for example "script": "auto".

params.name: data.login
params.description: Level of login required to access this resource. Not supported for Node.js in the App Engine standard environment.

params.name: data.auth_fail_action
params.description: Action to take when users access resources that require authentication. Defaults to redirect.

params.name: data.redirect_http_response_code
params.description: 30x code to use when performing redirects for the secure field. Defaults to 302.
